Draft multiple
{jjdpr_pace_s}
from one
{jjdhr_heat}
to another as a single atomic operation.
All
{jjdpr_pace_s}
receive new
{jjdt_coronet_s}
in the destination
{jjdhr_heat};
all
{jjdkr_tack}
history is preserved.

This operation mirrors
{jjdo_relocate}
behavior but operates on multiple
{jjdpr_pace_s}
atomically.
Either all
{jjdpr_pace_s}
transfer or none do.
Unlike
{jjdo_continue}
which has specific ceremony semantics (garlanding, alter, filtering by state),
{jjdo_transfer}
is a primitive bulk transfer: mechanical movement of specified
{jjdpr_pace_s}
with no additional ceremony.

{jjds_arguments}

//axd_required
* {jjdt_firemark}
— source
{jjdhr_heat}

//axd_required
* {jjda_to}
— destination
{jjdt_firemark}

//axd_required
* `coronets` (string) — JSON array of
{jjdt_coronet_s}
to draft (order preserved in destination)

{jjds_stdout} JSON object:

[source,json]
----
{
  "source": {
    "firemark": "AF",
    "silks": "jjk-restring-rust",
    "paddock": ".claude/jjm/jjp_AF.md",
    "empty_after": false
  },
  "destination": {
    "firemark": "AG",
    "silks": "jjk-alpha-launch",
    "paddock": ".claude/jjm/jjp_AG.md"
  },
  "drafted": [
