Tally family: three single-purpose {jjdpr_pace} mutation operations split from the original unified `jjx_tally` command.
Each mutates flat fields on the {jjdpr_pace} directly.

// tag::redocket[]
Update the docket text of one or more {jjdpr_pace_s}.
All input is provided via {jjdxo_gazette} `jjezs_reslate` notices.
No JSON params are required.

{jjds_arguments}

* {jjdt_coronet} and `docket` — provided via {jjdxo_gazette} `jjezs_reslate` notice lede and body.
Multiple notices in a single gazette enables mass reslate.

{jjds_stdout} Revision count and diffs.

{jjds_exit_uniform} 0 success, non-zero error.

{jjds_behavior}

. Parse {jjdxo_gazette} for one or more `jjezs_reslate` notices, each containing {jjdt_coronet} (lede) and docket text (body)
. {jjdr_load}; on failure, exit immediately with {jjdr_load} error status
. For each notice:
.. Extract parent {jjdt_firemark} from {jjdt_coronet} (first 2 base64 chars after prefix)
.. Verify {jjdhr_heat} exists
.. Verify {jjdpr_pace} exists with given {jjdt_coronet}
.. Update docket text on {jjdpr_pace}
. {jjdr_save}
// end::redocket[]

// tag::relabel[]
Change the {jjdt_silks} (display name) of a {jjdpr_pace}.

{jjds_arguments}

//axd_required
* {jjdt_coronet}

//axd_required
* {jjda_silks}

{jjds_stdout} None

{jjds_exit_uniform} 0 success, non-zero error.

{jjds_behavior}

. {jjdr_load}; on failure, exit immediately with {jjdr_load} error status
. Extract parent {jjdt_firemark} from {jjdt_coronet} (first 2 base64 chars after prefix)
. Verify {jjdhr_heat} exists
. Verify {jjdpr_pace} exists with given {jjdt_coronet}
. Update silks on {jjdpr_pace}
. {jjdr_save}
// end::relabel[]

// tag::drop[]
Mark a {jjdpr_pace} as {jjdpe_abandoned}. The {jjdpr_pace} is removed from active planning but remains in history.

{jjds_arguments}

//axd_required
* {jjdt_coronet}

{jjds_stdout} None

{jjds_exit_uniform} 0 success, non-zero error.

{jjds_behavior}

. {jjdr_load}; on failure, exit immediately with {jjdr_load} error status
. Extract parent {jjdt_firemark} from {jjdt_coronet} (first 2 base64 chars after prefix)
. Verify {jjdhr_heat} exists
. Verify {jjdpr_pace} exists with given {jjdt_coronet}
. Set state to {jjdpe_abandoned} on {jjdpr_pace}
. {jjdr_save}
// end::drop[]

